- Floor to ceiling glass frontage with an abundance of natural light

For more details or to arrange an inspection, please contact Amy Pfeiffer 0401 198 401.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: BE THE FACE OF THE GROVE SHOPPING CENTRE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
34 Grosvenor Street is very well located on the corner of Grosvenor and Young Streets, Neutral Bay.  Within close proximity to all of Neutral Bays amenity; including cafes, bus stops, retail strips, Woolworths as well as ease of parking for staff and clients.

Being located on the corner allows a corporate identity to be achieved, naming and signage opportunities and natural light from all four sides.  The fitout consists of reception area,  work areas into four sections, kitchen breakout area and male and female bathrooms.

There are 6 car parking spaces on-site allowing for a high car parking ratio of 1 space per 22 sqm.  Don't miss out on your chance to secure this unique offering.  For further details and to arrange an inspection contact:
Lisa Treble on 0411 542 497 or Michael Arcus on 0438 550 967
